.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Note that type of \fBinp\fP argument must be same as filter parameterized
input type (\fI\%IT\fP), i.e. \fI\%StringReplacer\fP is \fBIFilter[str, str]\fP type,
so you can apply it only to \fIstr\fP\-type inputs.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B Parameters
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
